Description: Part of a wooden coffin; paint on plaster; Hieroglyphic text in blue. According to Zitman (2010, 133 (II)) EA47607- 616, 617, 619 and 620 are the same object.
Excavator/field collector: Excavated by: Dr David George Hogarth
Bibliographic references: Zitman 2010 / The necropolis of Assiut: a case study of local Egyptian funerary culture from the Old Kingdom to the end of the Middle Kingdom (II, 133, 227)
